# Goal — what skill to run and how.
# ``skill_name`` picks a skill registered on the agent
# (e.g. ``navigate_to``, ``grasp``, ``move_to``).
# ``arguments_json`` is a JSON object string mapping kw -> value. Using
# a JSON string rather than a native ROS IDL field keeps the action
# generic: every skill the agent exposes maps onto this one action
# without needing its own message type.
string skill_name
string arguments_json
---
# Result — terminal outcome.
# ``ok`` mirrors ``GoalHandle`` SUCCEEDED; ``result_json`` carries the
# skill's structured result (room reached, object grasped, …).
bool ok
string result_json
string error
---
# Feedback — incremental progress.
# ``feedback_json`` is the same JSON as published on ``/agent_event``
# so subscribers can use either transport.
string feedback_json
